{
  "_comment": "ERP master-code + booking correction editor dictionary. Mirrors doc-fields.json's shape. One entry per correctable field, grouped by 'section'. The server (Handle-ErpEditSeed) reads each field's current value from the ERP column in 'readFrom' (suffix '..5' = join add1..add5; readFrom '' = derived/blank-seeded e.g. etd/eta/commodity-on-sea). For a 'code' field it resolves the current master NAME (custsub/linermstr/portmstr/servmstr) into the seed 'resolved' map so the editor shows 'code -> name (city, country)'. On save, ONLY changed fields are pushed to Swivel /booking/update by 'writeKey'. No writeKey => read-only.",
  "_kinds": "code=master code + lookup; text=free text; number=numeric (pushed as a JSON number); bool=tick (pushed as a real JSON boolean); date=ISO yyyy-mm-dd (pushed as the booking estimated-date key, API maps to the routing leg); ref=read-only display; table=container rows. writeKey 'bookingReference#PO' => pushed as bookingReference:[{refName:'PO',refDescription:value}].",
  "_fieldmap_verified": "2026-06-14 on live fm3khkg (HKG pilot); AIR re-verified 2026-06-14 on HAWB HKGAE6060004 (ref 62885, HKG->SEL->CHI->LAX). Routing row (both modes) = rece/pol/pod/dest, all editable chips (Air pod=first-leg discharge, e.g. SEL; the simple-route view). AIR carrier=rout_by_1 (carr is empty). AIR flight legs (compact, under Job No.) flight1/flight2/flight3 with discharges to1(display-only, =pod)/deli/to3 - leg1 flight1->voyageFlightNumber (to1 shown for context, NOT pushed - portOfDischargeCode is owned by the pod routing chip), leg2 deli->flexData.2ndLegPortOfDischargeCode + flight2->flexData.2ndLegFlightNumber, leg3 to3->flexData.3rdLegPortOfDischargeCode + flight3->flexData.3rdLegFlightNumber (IATA flexData, verified in 3rd-erpapi.json). AIR cargo: qty=t_rece_qty, gross=ttl_gwt, chargeable=ttl_cwt (->chargeableWeight), cbm=t_rece_cbm, unit=pkgs_unit. AIR marks/desc come from awbdetl.mark2/desc2 (header crmarking/wdesc are empty) - seeded server-side. Sea cargo totals t_book_qty/pkgs_unit/t_book_wgt/wgt_unit(default KGS)/t_book_cbm. SEA (verified 2026 on sono HK012606010, ref 24625): carrier=blhead.iliner; liner agent=blcont.lagent (party code on the container line, resolved to company name via custsub); finalDestination=blhead.dest, falls back to blhead.deli (Place of Delivery) when blank; commodity=blitem.commodity (NOT in blhead); container-size counts container20/40/HQ/Others=blitem.c20/c40/cq/c45; marks=blitem.mark2(+mark3), desc=blitem.good_desc1 else desc2(+desc3) - all server-seeded from blitem (blh=ref, first line). Air commodity=awbhead.commodity(ntext). PO=spotid(sea)/po_no(air). Containers blcont: container,cont_type,seal,load_qty,pkgs_unit,load_wgt,load_cbm. Trucker/broker/warehouse read-only (no booking-API field). No-of-originals=no_orig read-only (only telexRelease writable).",
  "_writekeys_confirmed": "Verified 2026-06-14 against Swivel 3rd-erpapi.json. bookingParty: shipper/consignee/notify(notifyPartyParty)/agent/linerAgent/controllingCustomer ...Code/Name/Address/ContactPhone/TaxCode. Top-level: incoTermsCode, serviceCode, placeOfReceiptCode, portOfLoadingCode, portOfDischargeCode, finalDestinationCode, carrierCode, carrierName, telexRelease(bool), isDirect(bool), dangerousGood(bool), divisionCode, picId, team, cargoReadyDateEstimated, cargoReceiptDateEstimated, departureDateEstimated(ETD), arrivalDateEstimated(ETA), commodity(maxlen 21), quantity(number), quantityUnit, grossWeight(number), weightUnit, cbm(number), shipMarks, goodsDescription, bookingReference[]{refName,refDescription}, bookingContainers[]{containerNo,soNo,sealNo,containerTypeCode,quantity,quantityUnit,weight,weightUnit,cbm}. Carrier + the estimated dates push best-effort (carrier master / date validation may reject - logged in erp_edit_log).",

